    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I hear you on the \"polish\" part, but I guess I'm looking for more practical guidance. For example, if a client has very textured or kinky hair, or if they wear religious headcoverings like a hijab, how do you suggest they navigate that? Some of the older partners at these firms still have very traditional views on what \"authority\" looks like—usually thinking of very smooth, groomed, or classic Western looks. Would you advise those clients to lean more towards smoothing their hair or styling it in a more \"standard\" way to avoid any unconscious bias from the board?",
